'''Loren Grey''' (1915 – 2007; born Middletown, New York) was an American novelist and educational psychologist who attended the USC [[Rossier School of Education]].
==Lassiter novels== * Lassiter (1985) * Ambush for Lassiter (1985) * Lassiter Gold (1986) * Lassiter Tough (1986) * The Lassiter Luck (1986) * A Grave for Lassiter (1987) * Lassiter's Ride (1988) * Lassiter on the Texas Trail (1988) * Lassiter and the Great Horse Race (1989) * Lassiter and the Golden Dragon (1989) * Lassiter's Showdown (1990) * Lassiter in the Comanche Stronghold (1990)
==References== *McLellan, Dennis, [https://web.archive.org/web/20110810221317/http://articles.latimes.com/2007/feb/16/local/me-grey16 ''Loren Grey, 91; son of writer Zane Grey was educational psychologist'']. ''Los Angeles Times''. Archived from the original on 29 June 2011.
